<TITLE> Law ministry seeks 2 more HC benches to hear NBR cases </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 14 (bdnews24.com)The law ministry will request the chief justice to constitute two new High Court benches to expeditiously dispose of about 17,500 long-pending NBR cases. Law minister Shafique Ahmed said disposing of these cases will pave the way for the government to realise Tk 7729 crore in revenue. Speaking to journalists after a meeting with the NBR chairman and the attorney general at his office on Sunday, Shafique said, "It has been decided to request the chief justice to set up two extra benches to dispose of about 17,500 cases hanging in the higher court." "These cases will eventually be settled by regular hearings by these two benches. On Monday a letter will be sent to the chief justice to take necessary steps in this regard." On October 1, NBR chairman Nasiruddin Ahmed held a meeting with the law minister on how to deal with the thousands of pending cases. Shafique said at that timea decision would be taken shortly. On Sunday, he said, "If need be, the existing laws will be amended to also allow for alternative means, like ADR, (alternative dispute resolution) to resolve the cases." "Both sides will be benefited through ADR," he said. b
